.cs 3 on
.item 'SET CURRENT Command' 'Updated on 11/14/82 by LSO'
.itemix "'SET * Command' . 'see SET CURRENT Command'"
.boxon
SET {CURRENT|*} [line-number] [EXECUTE]
.*              <-----------> <------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SET CURRENT line-number
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SET CURRENT EXECUTE
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SET CURRENT (or SET *) command sets the value of the symbolic line number,
CURRENT.  CURRENT and * are equivalent.  Type HELP CURRENT for a description
of CURRENT.

.* SELECT 'SET CURRENT Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION LINE-NUMBER
.optix line-number
line-number\\\\\specifies the line number value to which the symbolic line
                number CURRENT is to be set.  If this option is omitted,
                CURRENT is set to 0.

.* OPTION EXECUTE
.optix EXECUTE
EXECUTE\\\\\\\\\sets the value of the CURRENT symbolic line in the EXEC file
                instead of the active file.
.cs 3 off
